BinaryTree<T> - Class in src
This is the BinaryTree class which contains definitions of a BinaryTree and implements the BinaryTreeInterface A BinaryTree is just composed of a single BinaryNode, root, which is linked up to the rest of the tree.

A default constructor which simply sets the root to be null.

A constructor which takes preorder and inorder traversal Strings of a binary tree and uses that information to construct the tree.

BinaryTree(T, BinaryTree<T>, BinaryTree<T>) - Constructor for class src.BinaryTree
A constructor which sets the root BinaryNode to a BinaryNode which has data and left and right subtree (the subtrees can be null because this constructor delegates the creation of the object to a helper method "initializeTree".
